al careers. Alternately whimsical and tragic, wondering and brooding, trivial and profound, al-Tawhidi’s questions provoke an interaction as interesting in its spiritedness as in its content. This new edition of The Philosopher Responds is accompanied by the first full-length English translation of this important text, bringing this interaction to life for the English reader.A bilingual Arabic-English edition.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAuthors, ArabyTo 1258vCorrespondence. 0aIslamic philosophyvEarly works to 1800. 0aPhilosopherszIrany10th centuryvCorrespondence. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh1 aMiskawayh, Abū ʿAlī, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMontgomery, James E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOrfali, Bilal, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPomerantz, Maurice A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aVasalou, Sophia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479886999.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479886999423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479886999/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles